Rating: 4
I cut the cinnamon to 1/2 tsp, added a 1/2 tsp of nutmeg. I increased the habaneros to 3 (if it doesn't make the eyes water, it's not hot enough), used 2 Tb fresh thyme and cut back the allspice to 1 tsp. I eliminated the lime juice as well so I could marinate for 24 hours. The marinade keeps for up to a month. Hint to the cook that burned herself: oil your fingers well before handling hot chiles or don't seed them. I have used this marinade on peeled chunks of potato grilled over indirect heat for 30 minutes. Comes out great.

