Rating: 4
I LOVE jerk seasoning, but many will not. The intense scovilles will turn off a good bunch, and the agressive aromatics of spices like cinnamon and allspice will inspire either worship or loathing. This is a fine "wet" version. I would encourage all who love this recipe to dig up a "dry" rub recipe or invent one (based on substitution) to have a supply on hand for use at any time. Shrimp, chicken (especially dark meat) and pork tend to be my favorite uses for jerk, but beef is also a popular subject, and I would encourage people to use creativity if this range of flavors inspres them. I think the key to this dish is using freshly ground allspice. Try it with candied squash and braised greens.

