Rating: 4
Here's another idea for this great marinade... For Jerk Chicken Wings, prepare marinade as directed then place 5lbs of chicken wings in a Reynolds oven bag, pour the sauce over, tie the bag and cut 2-3 small slits for steam to release. Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes. The chicken is moist and falls off the bone...lovely. I prefer this method over the other jerk chicken wings recipe on file. *Addendum: Use the Large size bag and be sure to place the chicken wings in the bag on a cookie sheet or pan so that the bag does not touch any part of the oven..otherwise, enjoy your wings with a touch of noxious plastic seasoning.

